text: Starogard Gdański (; until 1950 Starogard, meaning "the old stronghold"; Pomeranian/; ) is a town in Pomeranian Voivodeship in northwestern Poland with 48,328 people living here in 2004.Michael Rademacher: Deutsche Verwaltungsgeschichte Westpreußen, Kreis Preußisch Stargard (2006).August Eduard Preuß: Preußische Landes- und Volkskunde.
